<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="96" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="37" pageNumber="96">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="37" pageNumber="96">
This species is distributed in northeastern Kazakhstan and the Xinjiang region in China. The species includes two subspecies: 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. r." pageId="37" pageNumber="96" rank="subSpecies" species="r." subSpecies="ribbei">P. r. ribbei</taxonomicName>
(Kraatz, 1878) and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. r." pageId="37" pageNumber="96" rank="subSpecies" species="r." subSpecies="bobrovi">P. r. bobrovi</taxonomicName>
, whose populations are separated by the Manrak and Saur Mountain ranges (
<bibRefCitation pageId="37" pageNumber="96">Toropov and Milko 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Danilevsky, ML" journalOrPublisher="International almanac" pageId="48" pageNumber="107" url="http://cerambycidae.net/catalog.pdf" year="2018 a">Danilevsky 2018a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Politodorcadion" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Politodorcadion ribbei" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="ribbei" subSpecies="bobrovi">Politodorcadion ribbei bobrovi</taxonomicName>
is endemic to Kazakhstan and occurs exclusively on the northern slopes of these mountains in the border zone with China. It inhabits clayey and stony semi-deserts in piedmont valleys with sparse grass vegetation. The larvae feed on various species of 
<taxonomicName family="Poaceae" lsidName="" pageId="37" pageNumber="96" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
. The adults are active from the end of April to the end of May (
<bibRefCitation pageId="37" pageNumber="96">Toropov and Milko 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
